  "market_context": "On the NASDAQ 100 5-minute chart, price made a strong impulsive move up, then began a retracement. Price could not close over the recent high and produced an aggressive move down that retested the old high before continuing lower into a prior fair value gap area.",
  "key_observation": "An old low sits within a fair value gap, acting as a PD array. As price reaches into that low inside the FVG, candles struggle to close lower, signalling the inducement is complete and an expansion higher is expected.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the strong impulsive move up on the NQ 5-minute chart and anticipate a retracement.",
    "Step 2: Observe price come up and fail to close over the recent high, then deliver an aggressive move down.",
    "Step 3: Note the retest of the old high followed by continued downside price action.",
    "Step 4: Locate the old low resting inside a fair value gap as the relevant PD array / inducement.",
    "Step 5: Watch the candles at that low and confirm they struggle to close lower into the FVG.",
    "Step 6: Anticipate a bullish expansion higher from the swept low inside the fair value gap."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "When a prior low sits inside a fair value gap, it serves as an inducement PD array. A sweep into that low with candles failing to close lower signals the manipulation is complete and sets up an expansion in the original direction.",
